In this example, the MyComponent component uses an if statement to determine whether to render a ‚ÄúLoading‚Ä¶‚Äù message or a ‚ÄúHello, world!‚Äù message, based on the value of the isLoading prop.

3 Ternary operator
You can also use the ternary operator ?: to conditionally render elements in a more concise way:


App.js

function MyComponent(props) {
  return props.isLoading ? <div>Loading...</div> : <div>Hello, world!</div>;
